<br>
I believe it's been posted that the XP bonus for groups will not be present here - they pretty well said that nine people, in two groups raided together, will get less xp overall than if they had just gone in together (unraided) and swapped mobs. I.E. I suspect if you are raided, all group xp bonuses will be gone from participating groups. Remember, raids are groups of groups. <br>
<br>
The main reason for it is to remove the KS group, to allow/control/improve looting (and the loot notifications), and give you a nice raid channel/box. The XP smoothing/loss is a side benefit. <br>
<br>
Might be ok for Ordo &quot;raids&quot; but we'd still likely group by level to maximize the XP. The new UI with custom channels removes all the comm issues we used to have.<br>
<br>
Good for Dragon and above raids tho.   <p>Mathir Thunderoak- Wood Elf Druid of Tunare // Taleen Bloodaxe - Barbarian Warrior of the Tribunal // Cendaar - Human Bard of Karana /// Ordo Ursi Prismatus - Lanys T'Vyl - EQ<BR><P align="right">
